scripts.text:
You stand before a colourful swirling phenomenon that is clearly a magical gateway of some sort, not dissimilar to the minor Gates that you used to travel between the Domains of the First Realm.

There is no immediate indication of where this one leads...

events.flavourText: You enter the dank chamber.  Small clumps of fungi give off a sickly radiance, and moving amongst the stalks are a number of large spiders.
The arachnids pause and regard you in silence for a moment.
Suddenly you feel a familiar sense of dissonance... the feeling of the Maze moving against you!
As one the spiders scuttle towards you, an uncanny malice glittering in their dark eyes.
Stepping through the door you find clouds of insects hovering near putrid pools of shallow water.
Suddenly you feel a familiar sense of dissonance... the feeling of the Maze moving against you!
In unnerving unison, the swarms rise from the pools and attack you!

scripts.text: Coming from behind this door is a faint hum. You pause to listen for a few moments, but no explanation is readily apparent.

events.flavourText: As you reach for the handle, something about this door makes you hesitate for a second...
Standing in the middle of the chamber is a stone statue of a chunky humanoid figure.
Suddenly you feel a familiar sense of dissonance... the feeling of the Maze moving against you!
The eyes of the stone construct flare to life and it lumbers towards you...
The dry bones of some long dead traveller lie here, huddled in this dark and dusty corner.
The eels scatter into the depths and vanish.

scripts.text: The pool of water in the alcove is deeper than the rest. You can't see the bottom, but you can see some movement beneath the surface...

Peering through the gloom, you can make out several large, pale eels circling lazily in the dark waters. 

They don't look dangerous. If you're quick enough, you may be able to grab one of them.

scripts.title: Try to grab an eel?

Gatehouse supplies 1 cave eels leave alone

events.flavourText: You leave the eels swimming in peace.

scripts.text:
Here you find a small stone shrine.

Shrines of the type are usually dedicated to Garret, The Grey Wayfarer, the ambivalent patron of heroes, adventurers and wayfarers; the cloaked one who stands guard before those who watch their own backs.
The portcullis is firmly closed. You do not see an obvious mechanism to open it...

Beneath the water of the shallow pool you spot a wide crack between the paving stones.

The crack is too dark and crooked to see anything. You could put an arm deep inside and explore, if you wanted to...

scripts.title: Explore the hole with your arm?

events.flavourText: You reach your arm deep into the cold, dark water...
Feeling along the bottom, your questing fingers brush a small cloth sack. Retrieving it you find some interesting contents.
You decide to leave well enough alone.

scripts.text:
The large lever mechanism looks tarnished and old but otherwise functional.

You wonder what hidden machinery it connects to...

events.flavourText: You give the lever a hard yank.
A loud clanking and grinding fills the dungeon.
With a flurry of wings, you are suddenly assaulted from above!

Peering through the bars, the room beyond is gloomy and quiet. A dank, feral smell faintly tickles your nose.

On the far side of the room you can just make out what looks like some kind of lever.

scripts.text: GATEHOUSE

events.flavourText: Above you a fixture on the ceiling gives off some kind of soft magical light.

events.journalText:
You have escaped from the First Realm of the Maze.
You seek now to escape from the Second.

Somewhere in this Realm you have entered lies a Great Gate. You must locate it, access it and pass through to escape this Realm and continue your journey to escape from the Maze entirely.

events.flavourText: ... you blink as the familiar disorientation of extradimensional travel wears off and your eyes adjust to the darkness. You appear to be in a gloomy stone corridor, and a dead end at that. The air is stale and heavy, and the oppresive silence is broken only by your breathing.

You look around. Some crudely etched runes on nearby walls emit a desultory glow, but otherwise this section of  corridor is unremarkable.
This gate seems to have been a one way trip: you can see no immediate way back to the First Realm from here...

scripts.text:
On the far wall of this large room you see what looks like two deactivated inter-domain portals. 

Before you can move over to get a close look, something else draws your urgent attention...

Shallow puddles dot this area of gloomy passageways, and the air is cold and humid.

You wonder where the leak is.
GATEHOUSE
A pile of dry and dusty bones has been heaped in this dark corner.

You brush cobwebs aside and peer nervously through the darkness. This area smells of mold, dust and fungus.

A spider, larger than the others, rouses itself angrily from a nest of bones in the far corner and moves to attack!

You brush cobwebs aside and peer nervously through the darkness. This area smells of mold, dust and fungus.

A spider, larger than the others, rouses itself angrily from a nest of bones in the far corner and moves to attack!
Swarming from the surrounding webbing, you are attacked by a group of disturbingly large spiders!
Something about this room seems intangibly different... maybe the air currents?
Large silky webs cover the walls and recede around the corner.
Swarming from the surrounding webbing, you are attacked by a group of disturbingly large spiders!
The portcullis is lowered and will not budge. You note a small lock mechanism with a keyhole near the ground...

This area of the dungeon is even dustier, gloomier and more run down than what you have seen so far.

From the darkness you seem to feel many eyes watching you through the strands of webbing.
A large web has been spun across the entrance to this alcove.

events.flavourText: With a loud *SPLAT* you hear something large and slimy drop to the ground behind you!

scripts.text: Unsurprisingly, the creator of the web is unimpressed with your intrusion.

You find a pile of very ancient very dry bones.
Maybe you should search them more carefully...
From behind the door you hear faint scraping and rustling noises.
This mushrooms growing in this corner look a bit different...

events.flavourText: You find a small, fierce looking creature rooting and scratching in the barrels in this room.
It freezes and meets your eyes. For a moment you have a frission of hope that the situation might be resolved non-violently ... but then the creature's eyes blaze with fury and it moves to attack!

scripts.text: The darkness here is relieved only by occasional luminous fungi. An earthen floor crunches under your feet, and the air is dank and heavy.
In a corner of the room you find a number of large, chitinous egg sacs.
These bones feel brittle and dry to the touch. Maybe you should search them more carefully...

maskTextureMouseClickScript.text:
Someone has carved a few lines in the stone wall here.

"Azael was here. A journey of a thousand leagues starts with one step."

events.flavourText: Quelling any misgivings about disturbing the remains, you decide to have a closer look.
Any clothing has long since rotted to pieces, but you do find two durable items.

The biscuits are very stale but still edible.
